name: Venonat
flavorText: Lives in the shadows of tall trees where it eats bugs. It is attracted by light at night.

name: Venomoth
flavorText: The wings are covered with dustlike scales. Every time it flaps its wings, it looses highly toxic dust.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, choose a Special Condition. Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now affected by that Special Condition.

name: Spinarak
flavorText: Although the poison from its fangs isn't that strong, it's potent enough to weaken prey that gets caught in its web.

name: Ariados
flavorText: It spews threads from its mouth to catch its prey. When night falls, it leaves its web to go hunt aggressively.
Ability1Text: Your opponent's Pokemon VSTAR's attacks cost Colorless more. You can't apply more than 1 Hidden Threads Ability at a time.

name: Sunkern
flavorText: It lives by drinking only dewdrops from under the leaves of plants. It is said that it eats nothing else.

name: Sunflora
flavorText: It gets energy from warm sunlight and is known for its habit of moving in pursuit of it.
Attack1Text: You may discard up to 3 Energy cards from your hand. This attack does 70 more damage for each card you discarded in this way.

name: Serperior V
Attack1Text: Heal 30 damage from each Pokemon (both yours and your opponent's).

name: Serperior VSTAR
Attack1Text: You may move any amount of Energy from your Pokemon to your other Pokemon in any way you like.
Attack2Text: This attack does 60 damage for each Energy attached to this Pokemon. Switch this Pokemon with 1 of your Benched Pokemon. (You can't use more than 1 VSTAR Power in a game.)

name: Petilil
flavorText: The leaves on its head are highly valued for medicinal purposes. Dry the leaves in the sun, boil them, and then drink the bitter decoction for remarkably effective relief from fatigue.

name: Hisuian Lilligant
flavorText: I suspect that its well-developed legs are the result of a life spent on mountains covered in deep snow. The scent it exudes from its flower crown heartens those in proximity.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 2 Grass Energy cards and attach them to your Benched Pokemon in any way you like. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Foongus
flavorText: No one knows what the Poke Ball–like pattern on Foongus means or why Foongus has it.

name: Amoonguss
flavorText: This Pokemon puffs poisonous spores at its foes. If the spores aren't washed off quickly, they'll grow into mushrooms wherever they land.
Ability1Text: During your opponent's turn, if this Pokemon is discarded from your hand by an effect of an attack or Ability from your opponent's Pokemon, or by an effect of your opponent's Item or Supporter cards, discard your opponent's hand.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Asleep.

name: Durant
flavorText: They lay their eggs deep inside their nests. When attacked by Heatmor, they retaliate using their massive mandibles.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 2 basic Energy cards, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Virizion
flavorText: A legend tells of this Pokemon working together with Cobalion and Terrakion to protect the Pokemon of the Unova region.
Attack1Text: If Cobalion, Terrakion, and Keldeo are on your Bench, this attack does 70 more damage.
Attack2Text: Heal 20 damage from this Pokemon.

name: Chesnaught V
Ability1Text: If your Active Chesnaught V is damaged by an attack from your opponent's Pokemon (even if it is Knocked Out), put 3 damage counters on the Attacking Pokemon.
Attack1Text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokemon.

name: Radiant Tsareena
flavorText: This feared Pokemon has long, slender legs and a cruel heart. It shows no mercy as it stomps on its opponents.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may heal 20 damage from each of your Pokemon.
Attack1Text: This Pokemon recovers from all Special Conditions.

name: Vulpix
flavorText: While young, it has six gorgeous tails. When it grows, several new tails are sprouted.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

name: Ninetales
flavorText: It is said to live 1,000 years, and each of its tails is loaded with supernatural powers.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Asleep.
Attack2Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon can't attack.

name: Growlithe
flavorText: It has a brave and trustworthy nature. It fearlessly stands up to bigger and stronger foes.

name: Arcanine
flavorText: The sight of it running over 6,200 miles in a single day and night has captivated many people.
Attack1Text: Attach a Fire Energy card from your discard pile to this Pokemon.
Attack2Text: If your opponent's Active Pokemon is a Pokemon V, this attack does 100 more damage.

name: Ponyta
flavorText: It can't run properly when it's newly born. As it races around with others of its kind, its legs grow stronger.
Attack1Text: This Pokemon also does 10 damage to itself.

name: Rapidash
flavorText: This Pokemon can be seen galloping through fields at speeds of up to 150 mph, its fiery mane fluttering in the wind.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may discard a Fire Energy card from your hand in order to use this Ability. During this turn, your Fire Pokemon's attacks do 30 more damage to your opponent's Active Pokemon (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Victini
flavorText: When it shares the infinite energy it creates, that being's entire body will be overflowing with power.
Attack1Text: Attach up to 2 Fire Energy cards from your discard pile to your Pokemon in any way you like.

name: Reshiram V
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 2 basic Energy cards and attach them to 1 of your Pokemon. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If tails, during your next turn, this Pokemon can't attack.

name: Fennekin
flavorText: As it walks, it munches on a twig in place of a snack. It intimidates opponents by puffing hot air out of its ears.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Supporter card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Braixen
flavorText: When the twig is plucked from its tail, friction sets the twig alight. The flame is used to send signals to its allies.
Attack2Text: This attack does 60 damage for each Serena card in your discard pile.

name: Delphox
flavorText: Using psychic power, it generates a fiery vortex of 5,400 degrees Fahrenheit, incinerating foes swept into this whirl of flame.
Attack1Text: This attack does 60 damage for each Serena card in your discard pile.
Attack2Text: This attack does 50 damage for each Energy attached to all of your opponent's Pokemon.

name: Fletchinder
flavorText: Fletchinder launches embers into the den of its prey. When the prey comes leaping out, Fletchinder's sharp talons finish it off.

name: Talonflame
flavorText: Talonflame mainly preys upon other bird Pokemon. To intimidate opponents, it sends embers spewing from gaps between its feathers.
Attack1Text: This attack does 50 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)
Attack2Text: If your opponent's Active Pokemon already has any damage counters on it, this attack does 80 more damage.

name: Litten
flavorText: Its coat regrows twice a year. When the time comes, Litten sets its own body on fire and burns away the old fur.
Attack2Text: This attack does 20 damage for each damage counter on this Pokemon.

name: Torracat
flavorText: When its mane is standing on end, you can tell it's feeling good. When it isn't feeling well, its fur will lie down flat.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, if this Pokemon has full HP and would be Knocked Out by damage from an attack, it is not Knocked Out, and its remaining HP becomes 10.

name: Incineroar
flavorText: When its fighting spirit is set alight, the flames around its waist become especially intense.
Attack1Text: Choose an attack from 1 of this Pokemon's previous Evolutions and use it as this attack.
Attack2Text: Discard all Energy from this Pokemon.

name: Alolan Vulpix V
Attack1Text: If your opponent's Active Pokemon is a Pokemon V, this attack does 50 more damage.

name: Alolan Vulpix VSTAR
Attack1Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by any effects on your opponent's Active Pokemon. During your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage done to this Pokemon by attacks from Pokemon that have an Ability.
Attack2Text: This attack does 70 damage for each of your opponent's Pokemon V in play. This damage isn't affected by Weakness or Resistance. (You can't use more than 1 VSTAR Power in a game.)

name: Omastar V
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 2 Pokemon that evolve from an Item card that has "Fossil" in its name and put them onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: If the Defending Pokemon is an Evolution Pokemon, it can't attack during your opponent's next turn.

name: Articuno
flavorText: It's said that this Pokemon's beautiful blue wings are made of ice. Articuno flies over snowy mountains, its long tail fluttering along behind it.
Attack2Text: This Pokemon also does 50 damage to itself. Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Wailmer
flavorText: It shows off by spraying jets of seawater from the nostrils above its eyes. It eats a solid ton of Wishiwashi every day.
Attack1Text: Heal from this Pokemon the same amount of damage you did to your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Wailord
flavorText: It can sometimes knock out opponents with the shock created by breaching and crashing its big body onto the water.
Ability1Text: This Pokemon takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack1Text: If this Pokemon has any Special Energy attached, this attack does 120 more damage.

name: Feebas
flavorText: Although unattractive and unpopular, this Pokemon's marvelous vitality has made it a subject of research.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a card that evolves from this Pokemon and put it onto this Pokemon to evolve it. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Milotic
flavorText: Milotic has provided inspiration to many artists. It has even been referred to as the most beautiful Pokemon of all.
Attack1Text: This attack does 50 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)
Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Asleep.

name: Snorunt
flavorText: It's said that if they are seen at midnight, they'll cause heavy snow. They eat snow and ice to survive.
Attack1Text: Draw a card.

name: Glalie
flavorText: It has a body of ice that won't melt, even with fire. It can instantly freeze moisture in the atmosphere.
Attack2Text: If you played Candice from your hand during this turn, this attack does 130 more damage.

name: Froslass
flavorText: After a woman met her end on a snowy mountain, her regrets lingered on. From them, this Pokemon was born. Its favorite food is frozen souls.
Attack1Text: If you played Candice from your hand during this turn, this attack does 90 more damage, and your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Relicanth
flavorText: Rock-hard scales and oil-filled swim bladders allow this Pokemon to survive the intense water pressure of the deep sea.
Attack1Text: Shuffle up to 4 in any combination of Unidentified Fossil and Rare Fossil cards from your discard pile into your deck.
Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Asleep.

name: Phione
flavorText: It drifts in warm seas. It always returns to where it was born, no matter how far it may have drifted.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 3 Basic Water Pokemon and put them onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Keldeo
flavorText: When it is resolute, its body fills with power and it becomes swifter. Its jumps are then too fast to follow.
Attack2Text: If Cobalion, Terrakion, and Virizion are on your Bench, this attack does 170 more damage.

name: Dewpider
flavorText: It forms a water bubble at the rear of its body and then covers its head with it. Meeting another Dewpider means comparing water-bubble sizes.

name: Araquanid
flavorText: It launches water bubbles with its legs, drowning prey within the bubbles. This Pokemon can then take its time to savor its meal.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed, and discard an Energy from that Pokemon.

name: Pikachu
flavorText: Pikachu that can generate powerful electricity have cheek sacs that are extra soft and super stretchy.
Attack1Text: If 1 of your Dedenne used Dede-Short during your last turn, this attack does 180 more damage.

name: Raichu
flavorText: Its long tail serves as a ground to protect itself from its own high-voltage power.
Attack1Text: If your opponent has used their VSTAR Power during this game, this attack does 100 more damage.

name: Chinchou
flavorText: Its antennae, which evolved from a fin, have both positive and negative charges flowing through them.

name: Lanturn
flavorText: The light it emits is so bright that it can illuminate the sea's surface from a depth of over three miles.
Attack2Text: Discard 2 Energy from this Pokemon.

name: Rotom
flavorText: One boy's invention led to the development of many different machines that take advantage of Rotom's unique capabilities.
Attack1Text: Shuffle your hand into your deck. Then, draw 6 cards.

name: Emolga
flavorText: As Emolga flutters through the air, it crackles with electricity. This Pokemon is cute, but it can cause a lot of trouble.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for an Item card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Stunfisk
flavorText: Thanks to bacteria that lived in the mud flats with it, this Pokemon developed the organs it uses to generate electricity.
Attack2Text: You can use this attack only if you have no Supporter cards in your discard pile. This attack does 100 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Zeraora
flavorText: It approaches its enemies at the speed of lightning, then tears them limb from limb with its sharp claws.
Attack1Text: If your opponent's Active Pokemon is an Evolution Pokemon, this attack does 30 more damage.

name: Regieleki V
Attack1Text: Switch this Pokemon with 1 of your Benched Pokemon.
Attack2Text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokemon takes 100 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Regieleki VMAX
Ability1Text: Your Basic Lightning Pokemon's attacks do 30 more damage to your opponent's Active Pokemon (before applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack1Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon can't attack.

name: Radiant Alakazam
flavorText: It has an incredibly high level of intelligence. Some say that Alakazam remembers everything that ever happens to it, from birth till death.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may move up to 2 damage counters from 1 of your opponent's Pokemon to another of their Pokemon.
Attack1Text: This attack does 20 damage for each card in your opponent's hand.

name: Drowzee
flavorText: It puts its prey to sleep and devours their dreams. It seems that bad dreams taste sour, so Drowzee doesn't particularly like eating them.
Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Asleep.

name: Hypno
flavorText: There are some Hypno that assist doctors with patients who can't sleep at night in hospitals.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 2 Stage 1 Pokemon and put them onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Jynx
flavorText: In certain parts of Galar, Jynx was once feared and worshiped as the Queen of Ice.
Ability1Text: If this Pokemon is Knocked Out by damage from an attack from your opponent's Pokemon V, your opponent can't take any Prize cards for it.
Attack1Text: This attack does 10 more damage for each damage counter on your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Misdreavus
flavorText: What makes it happy is imitating the voices of weeping people and scaring everyone. It doesn't deal well with folks who aren't easily frightened.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Confused.

name: Mismagius
flavorText: Its muttered curses can cause awful headaches or terrifying visions that torment others.
Ability1Text: If this Pokemon has full HP and is Knocked Out by damage from an attack from your opponent's Pokemon, put 8 damage counters on the Attacking Pokemon.
Attack1Text: Put 2 damage counters on each of your opponent's Pokemon.

name: Unown V
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Confused.
Attack2Text: If you use this attack when you have only 1 Prize card remaining, you win this game.

name: Unown VSTAR
Attack1Text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 70 damage for each heads.
Attack2Text: Until this Pokemon leaves play, it gains an Ability that has the effect "The Weakness of each of your opponent's Pokemon in play is now Psychic. (The amount of Weakness doesn't change.)" (You can't use more than 1 VSTAR Power in a game.)

name: Ralts
flavorText: It is highly attuned to the emotions of people and Pokemon. It hides if it senses hostility.
Attack1Text: Choose 1 of your opponent's Active Pokemon's attacks. During your opponent's next turn, that Pokemon can't use that attack.

name: Kirlia
flavorText: If its Trainer becomes happy, it overflows with energy, dancing joyously while spinning about.
Ability1Text: You must discard a card from your hand in order to use this Ability. Once during your turn, you may draw 2 cards.

name: Gardevoir
flavorText: It has the power to predict the future. Its power peaks when it is protecting its Trainer.
Ability1Text: You must discard a card from your hand in order to use this Ability. Once during your turn, you may draw 2 cards.

name: Mawile V
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Discard a random card from your opponent's hand.

name: Mawile VSTAR
Ability1Text: During your turn, if this Pokemon is on your Bench, you may switch it with your Active Pokemon. If you do, switch 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon with their Active Pokemon. (You can't use more than 1 VSTAR Power in a game.)
Attack1Text: If this Pokemon moved from your Bench to the Active Spot this turn, this attack does 90 more damage.

name: Meditite
flavorText: It eats just one berry a day. By enduring hunger, its spirit is tempered and made sharper.
Ability1Text: As long as this Pokemon is on your Bench, prevent all damage done to this Pokemon by attacks (both yours and your opponent's).

name: Medicham
flavorText: Through yoga training, it gained the psychic power to predict its foe's next move.
Ability1Text: If you have exactly 4 cards in your hand, this Pokemon's attacks cost ColorlessColorlessColorless less.
Attack1Text: If your opponent has any Pokemon VMAX in play, this attack does 90 more damage.

name: Chimecho
flavorText: Emitting ultrasonic cries, it floats on winds to travel great distances.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, if an Energy card is attached to the Defending Pokemon from your opponent's hand, that Pokemon will be Asleep.

name: Sigilyph
flavorText: Psychic power allows these Pokemon to fly. Some say they were the guardians of an ancient city. Others say they were the guardians' emissaries.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Basic Pokemon and put it onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck. If your opponent's Active Pokemon is a Pokemon V, you may put up to 5 Basic Pokemon onto your Bench in this way instead.

name: Solosis
flavorText: It communicates with others telepathically. Its body is encapsulated in liquid, but if it takes a heavy blow, the liquid will leak out.

name: Duosion
flavorText: Its psychic power can supposedly cover a range of more than half a mile—but only if its two brains can agree with each other.
Attack1Text: Put 2 damage counters on 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon.

name: Reuniclus
flavorText: While it could use its psychic abilities in battle, this Pokemon prefers to swing its powerful arms around to beat opponents into submission.
Ability1Text: If this Pokemon is Knocked Out by damage from an attack from your opponent's Pokemon, put it into your hand instead of the discard pile. (Discard all attached cards.)
Attack1Text: Choose 2 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon and put 3 damage counters on each of them.

name: Elgyem
flavorText: If this Pokemon stands near a TV, strange scenery will appear on the screen. That scenery is said to be from its home.

name: Beheeyem
flavorText: Whenever a Beheeyem visits a farm, a Dubwool mysteriously disappears.
Attack2Text: This attack does 60 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokemon. Also apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.

name: Espurr
flavorText: Though Espurr's expression never changes, behind that blank stare is an intense struggle to contain its devastating psychic power.

name: Meowstic
flavorText: Females are a bit more selfish and aggressive than males. If they don't get what they want, they will torment you with their psychic abilities.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokemon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokemon during your turn, you may search your deck for up to 2 Supporter cards, reveal them, and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Swirlix
flavorText: It eats its own weight in sugar every day. If it doesn't get enough sugar, it becomes incredibly grumpy.

name: Slurpuff
flavorText: By taking in a person's scent, it can sniff out their mental and physical condition. It's hoped that this skill will have many medical applications.
Attack1Text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokemon.

name: Dedenne
flavorText: A Dedenne's whiskers pick up electrical waves other Dedenne send out. These Pokemon share locations of food or electricity with one another.
Attack2Text: You can use this attack only if 1 of your Togedemaru used Toge Dash during your last turn. Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Indeedee
flavorText: These intelligent Pokemon touch horns with each other to share information between them.
Attack1Text: If you go first, you can use this attack during your first turn. Search your deck for a card and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Dreepy
flavorText: After being reborn as a ghost Pokemon, Dreepy wanders the areas it used to inhabit back when it was alive in prehistoric seas.
Attack1Text: This Pokemon also does 10 damage to itself.

name: Drakloak
flavorText: It's capable of flying faster than 120 mph. It battles alongside Dreepy and dotes on them until they successfully evolve.

name: Dragapult
flavorText: When it isn't battling, it keeps Dreepy in the holes on its horns. Once a fight starts, it launches the Dreepy like supersonic missiles.
Attack1Text: Discard a number of your Benched Dreepy up to the number of your opponent's Pokemon in play. Then, for each Dreepy you discarded in this way, choose 1 of your opponent's Pokemon and do 100 damage to it. You can't choose the same Pokemon more than once. This damage isn't affected by Weakness or Resistance.

name: Hisuian Arcanine V
Ability1Text: As often as you like during your turn, you may move a Fighting Energy from 1 of your other Pokemon to this Pokemon.
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 more damage for each Fighting Energy attached to this Pokemon.

name: Phanpy
flavorText: It is strong despite its compact size. It can easily pick up and carry an adult human on its back.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 20 more damage.

name: Donphan
flavorText: The longer and bigger its tusks, the higher its rank in its herd. The tusks take long to grow.
Attack1Text: If this Pokemon evolved during this turn, this attack does nothing.

name: Baltoy
flavorText: It moves while spinning around on its single foot. Some Baltoy have been seen spinning on their heads.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Pokemon, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Claydol
flavorText: This mysterious Pokemon started life as an ancient clay figurine made over 20,000 years ago.
Ability1Text: You can use this Ability only if you have no Supporter cards in your discard pile. Once during your turn, you may attach a Fighting Energy card from your discard pile to 1 of your Pokemon.

name: Anorith
flavorText: This Pokemon was restored from a fossil. Anorith lived in the ocean about 100,000,000 years ago, hunting with its pair of claws.
Attack1Text: You may discard an Unidentified Fossil card from your hand. If you do, this attack does 120 more damage.

name: Armaldo
flavorText: After evolution, this Pokemon emerged onto land. Its lower body has become stronger, and blows from its tail are devastating.
Attack1Text: If your opponent's Active Pokemon has 100 HP or less remaining, it is Knocked Out.

name: Terrakion
flavorText: It has phenomenal power. It will mercilessly crush anyone or anything that bullies small Pokemon.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage from attacks done to this Pokemon. If 1 of your Pokemon used Cavern Tackle during your last turn, this attack can't be used.

name: Hawlucha
flavorText: It drives its opponents to exhaustion with its agile maneuvers, then ends the fight with a flashy finishing move.
Attack1Text: Draw 2 cards.
Attack2Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 20 more damage for each heads.

name: Sandygast
flavorText: Grudges of the dead have possessed a mound of sand and become a Pokemon. Sandygast is fond of the shovel on its head.
Attack1Text: During your opponent's next turn, the Defending Pokemon can't retreat.

name: Palossand
flavorText: Palossand is known as the Beach Nightmare. It pulls its prey down into the sand by controlling the sand itself, and then it sucks out their souls.
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 damage to each of your opponent's Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Stonjourner
flavorText: It stands in grasslands, watching the sun's descent from zenith to horizon. This Pokemon has a talent for delivering dynamic kicks.
Attack2Text: If you have no Supporter cards in your discard pile, this attack does 130 more damage.

name: Ursaluna V
Ability1Text: This Pokemon takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack1Text: This attack does 10 less damage for each damage counter on this Pokemon.

name: Zubat
flavorText: It emits ultrasonic waves from its mouth to check its surroundings. Even in tight caves, Zubat flies around with skill.

name: Golbat
flavorText: It loves to drink other creatures' blood. It's said that if it finds others of its kind going hungry, it sometimes shares the blood it's gathered.

name: Crobat
flavorText: Both of its legs have turned into wings. Without a sound, Crobat flies swiftly toward its prey and sinks its fangs into the nape of its target's neck.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Poisoned.
Attack2Text: This attack does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.) If 1 of your opponent's Pokemon is Knocked Out by damage from this attack, take 2 more Prize cards.

name: Murkrow
flavorText: It searches for shiny things for its boss. Murkrow's presence is said to be unlucky, so many people detest it.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 2 Murkrow and put them onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Honchkrow
flavorText: Its goons take care of most of the fighting for it. The only time it dirties its own hands is in delivering a final blow to finish off an opponent.
Attack1Text: Draw 3 cards.
Attack2Text: You may switch this Pokemon with 1 of your Benched Murkrow.

name: Skuntank V
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. If that Pokemon retreated from the Active Spot during your opponent's last turn, this attack does 120 damage instead. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)
Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Confused and Poisoned.

name: Croagunk
flavorText: It makes frightening noises with its poison-filled cheek sacs. When opponents flinch, Croagunk hits them with a poison jab.

name: Toxicroak
flavorText: It bounces toward opponents and gouges them with poisonous claws. No more than a scratch is needed to knock out its adversaries.
Attack2Text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokemon takes 50 more damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Sandile
flavorText: The desert gets cold at night, so when the sun sets, this Pokemon burrows deep into the sand and sleeps until sunrise.

name: Krokorok
flavorText: Krokorok has specialized eyes that enable it to see in the dark. This ability lets Krokorok hunt in the dead of night without getting lost.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Krookodile
flavorText: This Pokemon is known as the Bully of the Sands. Krookodile's mighty jaws can bite through heavy plates of iron with almost no effort at all.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokemon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokemon during your turn, you may discard a random card from your opponent's hand. If this Pokemon is your Active Pokemon and is Knocked Out by damage from an opponent's attack, you may discard a random card from your opponent's hand.
Attack1Text: This Pokemon also does 30 damage to itself.

name: Mareanie
flavorText: The first symptom of its sting is numbness. The next is an itching sensation so intense that it's impossible to resist the urge to claw at your skin.
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Poisoned.

name: Toxapex
flavorText: To survive in the cold waters of Galar, this Pokemon forms a dome with its legs, enclosing its body so it can capture its own body heat.
Attack1Text: If your opponent's Active Pokemon is Poisoned, this attack does 120 more damage.

name: Morpeko
flavorText: Intense hunger drives it to extremes of violence, and the electricity in its cheek sacs has converted into a Dark-type energy.
Attack1Text: You can use this attack only if 1 of your Dedenne used Dede-Short during your last turn. This attack does 60 damage to each of your opponent's Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Beldum
flavorText: From its rear, Beldum emits a magnetic force that rapidly pulls opponents in. They get skewered on Beldum's sharp claws.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a card. Shuffle your deck, then put that card on top of it.

name: Metang
flavorText: Two Beldum have become stuck together via their own magnetic forces. With two brains, the resulting Metang has doubled psychic powers.
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 30 more damage for each heads.

name: Metagross
flavorText: Because the magnetic powers of these Pokemon get stronger in freezing temperatures, Metagross living on snowy mountains are full of energy.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, if you drew this Pokemon from your deck at the beginning of your turn and your Bench isn't full, before you put it into your hand, you may put it onto your Bench. If you do, draw 3 cards.
Attack1Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon's Meteor Mash attack does 100 more damage (before applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Radiant Jirachi
flavorText: It is said to have the ability to grant any wish for just one week every thousand years.
Ability1Text: If this Pokemon is in the Active Spot and is Knocked Out by damage from an attack from your opponent's Pokemon, search your deck for up to 3 cards and put them into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. If both of them are heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is Knocked Out.

name: Ferroseed
flavorText: It defends itself by launching spikes, but its aim isn't very good at first. Only after a lot of practice will it improve.

name: Ferrothorn
flavorText: This Pokemon scrapes its spikes across rocks, and then uses the tips of its feelers to absorb the nutrients it finds within the stone.

name: Klink
flavorText: The two minigears that compose this Pokemon are closer than twins. They mesh well only with each other.
Attack1Text: Search your deck for a Pokemon, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Klang
flavorText: When Klang goes all out, the minigear links up perfectly with the outer part of the big gear, and this Pokemon's rotation speed increases sharply.
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 80 damage for each heads.

name: Klinklang
flavorText: From its spikes, it launches powerful blasts of electricity. Its red core contains an enormous amount of energy.
Ability1Text: When you play this Pokemon from your hand to evolve 1 of your Pokemon during your turn, you may search your deck for up to 3 basic Energy cards and attach them to your Pokemon in any way you like. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Cobalion
flavorText: This Pokemon appears in a legend alongside Terrakion and Virizion, fighting against humans in defense of the Unova region's Pokemon.
Ability1Text: Your Basic Pokemon's attacks do 30 more damage to your opponent's Active Darkness Pokemon (before applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack1Text: Choose up to 2 of your Benched Pokemon. For each of those Pokemon, search your deck for a basic Energy card and attach it to that Pokemon. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Togedemaru
flavorText: With the long hairs on its back, this Pokemon takes in electricity from other electric Pokemon. It stores what it absorbs in an electric sac.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, during your opponent's next turn, if this Pokemon is Knocked Out, your opponent can't take any Prize cards for it.

name: Magearna V
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)
Attack2Text: If this Pokemon has any Special Energy attached, this attack does 120 more damage.

name: Dratini
flavorText: Dratini dwells near bodies of rapidly flowing water, such as the plunge pools of waterfalls. As it grows, Dratini will shed its skin many times.
Attack1Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 30 damage for each heads.

name: Dragonair
flavorText: This Pokemon lives in pristine oceans and lakes. It can control the weather, and it uses this power to fly into the sky, riding on the wind.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Paralyzed.

name: Dragonite
flavorText: It's a kindhearted Pokemon. If it spots a drowning person or Pokemon, Dragonite simply must help them.
Attack2Text: Search your deck for up to 3 basic Energy cards and attach them to your Pokemon in any way you like. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Noibat
flavorText: After nightfall, they emerge from the caves they nest in during the day. Using their ultrasonic waves, they go on the hunt for ripened fruit.

name: Noivern
flavorText: Aggressive and cruel, this Pokemon will ruthlessly torment enemies that are helpless in the dark.
Attack1Text: Knock Out 1 of your opponent's Radiant Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Draw cards until you have 7 cards in your hand.

name: Zygarde
flavorText: Born when around 10% of Zygarde's cells have been gathered from all over, this form is skilled in close-range combat.
Attack1Text: Attach a basic Energy card from your discard pile to 1 of your Benched Pokemon.

name: Regidrago V
Attack1Text: Discard the top 3 cards of your deck. If any of those cards are Energy cards, attach them to this Pokemon.
Attack2Text: This attack also does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Regidrago VSTAR
Ability1Text: During your turn, you may discard the top 7 cards of your deck. Then, put up to 2 cards from your discard pile into your hand. (You can't use more than 1 VSTAR Power in a game.)
Attack1Text: Choose an attack from a Dragon Pokemon in your discard pile and use it as this attack.

name: Smeargle
flavorText: It draws symbols with the fluid that oozes from the tip of its tail. Depending on the symbol, Smeargle fanatics will pay big money for them.
Attack1Text: Look at the top 5 cards of your deck. You may attach any number of basic Energy cards you find there to 1 of your Pokemon. Shuffle the other cards back into your deck.

name: Lugia V
Attack1Text: Discard a card from your hand. If you do, draw 3 cards.
Attack2Text: You may discard a Stadium in play.

name: Lugia VSTAR
Ability1Text: During your turn, you may put up to 2 Colorless Pokemon that don't have a Rule Box from your discard pile onto your Bench. (Pokemon V, Pokemon-GX, etc. have Rule Boxes.) (You can't use more than 1 VSTAR Power in a game.)
Attack1Text: You may discard a Stadium in play.

name: Ho-Oh V
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, if this Pokemon is in your discard pile, you may put it onto your Bench. If you do, attach up to 4 basic Energy cards from your discard pile to this Pokemon. If you use this Ability, your turn ends.
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 more damage for each type of basic Energy attached to this Pokemon.

name: Spinda
flavorText: Each Spinda's spot pattern is different. With its stumbling movements, it evades opponents' attacks brilliantly!
Attack1Text: This attack does 10 damage to each of your opponent's Pokemon. Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Confused. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

name: Swablu
flavorText: Its cottony wings are full of air, making them light and fluffy to the touch. Swablu takes diligent care of its wings.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin until you get tails. This attack does 20 damage for each heads.

name: Altaria
flavorText: As it flies in a calm and relaxed manner, Altaria performs a humming song that would enrapture any audience.
Attack1Text: Move all damage counters from 1 of your Benched Pokemon to your opponent's Active Pokemon.

name: Buneary
flavorText: If both of Buneary's ears are rolled up, something is wrong with its body or mind. It's a sure sign the Pokemon is in need of care.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If tails, this attack does nothing.

name: Lopunny
flavorText: Lopunny is constantly monitoring its surroundings. If danger approaches, this Pokemon responds with superdestructive kicks.
Attack2Text: Flip 2 coins. This attack does 100 damage for each heads.

name: Archen
flavorText: This Pokemon was successfully restored from a fossil. As research suggested, Archen is unable to fly. But it's very good at jumping.

name: Archeops
flavorText: It needs a running start to take off. If Archeops wants to fly, it first needs to run nearly 25 mph, building speed over a course of about 2.5 miles.
Ability1Text: Once during your turn, you may search your deck for up to 2 Special Energy cards and attach them to 1 of your Pokemon. Then, shuffle your deck.

name: Rufflet
flavorText: Its chick-like looks belie its hotheadedness. It challenges its parents at every opportunity, desperate to prove its strength.
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, this attack does 30 more damage.

name: Hisuian Braviary
flavorText: Screaming a bloodcurdling battle cry, this huge and ferocious bird Pokemon goes out on the hunt. It blasts lakes with shock waves, then scoops up any prey that float to the water's surface.
Attack1Text: Put 3 damage counters on each of your opponent's Pokemon that has any damage counters on it.
Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Confused.

name: Fletchling
flavorText: Its melodious cries are actually warnings. Fletchling will mercilessly peck at anything that enters its territory.

name: Earthen Seal Stone
Attack1Text: Put damage counters on each of your opponent's Pokemon V until its remaining HP is 100. (You can't use more than 1 VSTAR Power in a game.)

name: Forest Seal Stone
Ability1Text: During your turn, you may search your deck for a card and put it into your hand. Then, shuffle your deck. (You can't use more than 1 VSTAR Power in a game.)

name: Serperior V
Attack1Text: Heal 30 damage from each Pokemon (both yours and your opponent's).

name: Chesnaught V
Ability1Text: If your Active Chesnaught V is damaged by an attack from your opponent's Pokemon (even if it is Knocked Out), put 3 damage counters on the Attacking Pokemon.
Attack1Text: Heal 30 damage from this Pokemon.

name: Reshiram V
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 2 basic Energy cards and attach them to 1 of your Pokemon. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: Flip a coin. If tails, during your next turn, this Pokemon can't attack.

name: Alolan Vulpix V
Attack1Text: If your opponent's Active Pokemon is a Pokemon V, this attack does 50 more damage.

name: Omastar V
Attack1Text: Search your deck for up to 2 Pokemon that evolve from an Item card that has "Fossil" in its name and put them onto your Bench. Then, shuffle your deck.
Attack2Text: If the Defending Pokemon is an Evolution Pokemon, it can't attack during your opponent's next turn.

name: Regieleki V
Attack1Text: Switch this Pokemon with 1 of your Benched Pokemon.
Attack2Text: During your opponent's next turn, this Pokemon takes 100 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).

name: Unown V
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Confused.
Attack2Text: If you use this attack when you have only 1 Prize card remaining, you win this game.

name: Unown V
Attack1Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Confused.
Attack2Text: If you use this attack when you have only 1 Prize card remaining, you win this game.

name: Mawile V
Attack1Text: Flip a coin. If heads, discard an Energy from your opponent's Active Pokemon.
Attack2Text: Discard a random card from your opponent's hand.

name: Hisuian Arcanine V
Ability1Text: As often as you like during your turn, you may move a Fighting Energy from 1 of your other Pokemon to this Pokemon.
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 more damage for each Fighting Energy attached to this Pokemon.

name: Skuntank V
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. If that Pokemon retreated from the Active Spot during your opponent's last turn, this attack does 120 damage instead. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)
Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Confused and Poisoned.

name: Skuntank V
Attack1Text: This attack does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. If that Pokemon retreated from the Active Spot during your opponent's last turn, this attack does 120 damage instead. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)
Attack2Text: Your opponent's Active Pokemon is now Confused and Poisoned.

Attack1Text: This attack does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)
Attack2Text: If this Pokemon has any Special Energy attached, this attack does 120 more damage.

Attack1Text: Discard the top 3 cards of your deck. If any of those cards are Energy cards, attach them to this Pokemon.
Attack2Text: This attack also does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

Attack1Text: Discard the top 3 cards of your deck. If any of those cards are Energy cards, attach them to this Pokemon.
Attack2Text: This attack also does 30 damage to 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon. (Don't apply Weakness and Resistance for Benched Pokemon.)

Attack1Text: Discard a card from your hand. If you do, draw 3 cards.
Attack2Text: You may discard a Stadium in play.

Attack2Text: You may discard a Stadium in play.

Attack1Text: This attack does 30 more damage for each type of basic Energy attached to this Pokemon.

name: Serperior VSTAR
Attack1Text: You may move any amount of Energy from your Pokemon to your other Pokemon in any way you like.
Attack2Text: This attack does 60 damage for each Energy attached to this Pokemon. Switch this Pokemon with 1 of your Benched Pokemon. (You can't use more than 1 VSTAR Power in a game.)

name: Alolan Vulpix VSTAR
Attack1Text: This attack's damage isn't affected by any effects on your opponent's Active Pokemon. During your opponent's next turn, prevent all damage done to this Pokemon by attacks from Pokemon that have an Ability.
Attack2Text: This attack does 70 damage for each of your opponent's Pokemon V in play. This damage isn't affected by Weakness or Resistance. (You can't use more than 1 VSTAR Power in a game.)

name: Regieleki VMAX
Ability1Text: Your Basic Lightning Pokemon's attacks do 30 more damage to your opponent's Active Pokemon (before applying Weakness and Resistance).
Attack1Text: During your next turn, this Pokemon can't attack.

name: Unown VSTAR
Attack1Text: Flip 3 coins. This attack does 70 damage for each heads.
Attack2Text: Until this Pokemon leaves play, it gains an Ability that has the effect "The Weakness of each of your opponent's Pokemon in play is now Psychic. (The amount of Weakness doesn't change.)" (You can't use more than 1 VSTAR Power in a game.)

name: Mawile VSTAR
Ability1Text: During your turn, if this Pokemon is on your Bench, you may switch it with your Active Pokemon. If you do, switch 1 of your opponent's Benched Pokemon with their Active Pokemon. (You can't use more than 1 VSTAR Power in a game.)
Attack1Text: If this Pokemon moved from your Bench to the Active Spot this turn, this attack does 90 more damage.

name: Regidrago VSTAR
Ability1Text: During your turn, you may discard the top 7 cards of your deck. Then, put up to 2 cards from your discard pile into your hand. (You can't use more than 1 VSTAR Power in a game.)

Attack1Text: You may discard a Stadium in play.
